    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a8aca562_7154ffa1",
        "filename": "src/power_controller.rs",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 78,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000159
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-03-20T13:13:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Having overlapping multi-bit flags is not recommended in bitflags: https://docs.rs/bitflags/2.9.0/bitflags/#multi-bit-flags\nThis should be handled separately:\n* Define a PowerOnReason enum\n* Add power_on_reason(\u0026mut self, mpidr : u32) -\u003e PowerOnReason for querying this field of the SysStatusRegister.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "85512bfeddb877b56ea3c056239433c92909d8ba",
      "serverId": "8f6f209b-db1a-4cbf-aa44-c8bc30e9bfda"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e4e9b15f_bfee3db6",
        "filename": "src/power_controller.rs",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 78,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001350
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-03-20T16:45:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The only thing is that this way we have to make 2 different writes and reads for the reading the same register.\nI could get avoid this by making the system_status function return both `PowerOnReason` and `SysStatusRegister`?\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "a8aca562_7154ffa1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "85512bfeddb877b56ea3c056239433c92909d8ba",
      "serverId": "8f6f209b-db1a-4cbf-aa44-c8bc30e9bfda"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3f5cd48_cdcba934",
        "filename": "src/power_controller.rs",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 78,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000159
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-03-24T11:28:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is fine two have two separate functions for these, because these pieces of information are somewhat unrelated. The power on reason is relevant for the early boot code when it checks if this is a cold boot. The system status is used by the PSCI platform implementation.\nIn other words these two functions are not likely to be called one after the other so this doesn\u0027t introduce an overhead.\nYou can also define a private function for reading `psysr` as a u32 and then call it in the individual functions.",
      "parentUuid": "e4e9b15f_bfee3db6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "85512bfeddb877b56ea3c056239433c92909d8ba",
      "serverId": "8f6f209b-db1a-4cbf-aa44-c8bc30e9bfda"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
